  "body": "Hi, \n\nI'm using `LinkedStateMixin` for my `<input>`s with an initial value coming from `props`.  The problem is, when I use `autoFocus` on that `<input>`, the cursor shows up in the front of the field rather than at the end of the existing text.\n\nHere's what my component looks like:\n\n``` javascript\nvar ControlledInput = React.createClass({\n  mixins: [React.addons.LinkedStateMixin],\n  render: function() {\n        return <input ref=\"input\" autoFocus={true} valueLink={this.linkState('message')} />;\n    },\n\n  getInitialState: function () {\n    return {message: this.props.message};\n  },\n\n  componentWillReceiveProps: function (nextProps) {\n    if ( nextProps.message != this.props.message ) {\n      this.setState({message: nextProps.message});\n    }\n  }\n});\n```\n",
